.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH generate 1  "generate " 
.SH NAME
generate \- Générer les fichiers man et completions shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgenerate\fR [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIWHAT\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Générer les fichiers man et completions shell
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: generated]
Répertoire de sortie (défaut: ./generated)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIWHAT\fR>
Type: man, completions, all
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
man: Pages man
.IP \(bu 2
completions: Completions shell (bash, zsh, fish)
.IP \(bu 2
all: Tout générer
.RE
